OASISFormat: 0.3
Name: uunf
Version: 0.9.0
Synopsis: Unicode text normalization for OCaml
Authors: Daniel Bünzli <daniel.buenzli at erratique.ch>
Copyrights: (c) 2012 Daniel C. Bünzli
License: BSD3
Homepage: http://erratique.ch/software/uunf
Description:
 Uunf is an OCaml module for normalizing Unicode text. It supports all
 Unicode [normalization forms][1]. The module is independent from any IO
 mechanism or Unicode text data structure and it can process text without 
 a complete in-memory representation.
 .  
 Uunf is made of a single independent module and distributed under the
 BSD3 license.
 .
 [1]: http://www.unicode.org/reports/tr15/
OCamlVersion: >= 3.12.0
